TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Note on the Multi-Commodity Warehouse Problem
AU  - Eastman, Willard L.
Y1  - 1959/04/01
PY  - 1959
DA  - 1959/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.5.3.327
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.5.3.327
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 327
EP  - 331
VL  - 5
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The warehouse problem requires the determination of a sequence of buy and sell decisions at discrete points in time. By equating points in time and points in space, the warehouse problem can be identified with a special case of the shortest-route problem. In the present note a special matrix formulation is employed to yield simple solutions to both problems. An example is included to illustrate the method.
AB  - The warehouse problem requires the determination of a sequence of buy and sell decisions at discrete points in time. By equating points in time and points in space, the warehouse problem can be identified with a special case of the shortest-route problem. In the present note a special matrix formulation is employed to yield simple solutions to both problems. An example is included to illustrate the method.
