TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Note on Professor Manne's “Dominance” Theorem
AU  - Levitan, R. E.
Y1  - 1959/04/01
PY  - 1959
DA  - 1959/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.5.3.332
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.5.3.332
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 332
EP  - 334
VL  - 5
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Professor Manne's paper recently appearing in this Journal (Manne, A. S. 1958. Programming of economic lot sizes. Management Sci. 4 (2, January).) is an ingenious application of linear programming technique to what may have hitherto been regarded as an intractable non linear situation. The excellences of the paper are, however, marred by a gap in the proof of the ?Dominance? theorem. It is the aim of this communication to point out that, although the constructive proof offered by Manne is vulnerable to counter-example, an alternative, fairly simple, proof can be given. The theorem being true, the important results of the paper are not weakend.
AB  - Professor Manne's paper recently appearing in this Journal (Manne, A. S. 1958. Programming of economic lot sizes. Management Sci. 4 (2, January).) is an ingenious application of linear programming technique to what may have hitherto been regarded as an intractable non linear situation. The excellences of the paper are, however, marred by a gap in the proof of the ?Dominance? theorem. It is the aim of this communication to point out that, although the constructive proof offered by Manne is vulnerable to counter-example, an alternative, fairly simple, proof can be given. The theorem being true, the important results of the paper are not weakend.
